<br>
The other thing about routers in general is that they have to be configured. IP routing isn't that tough if you understand the protocols, but if you don't, a bad route table can really screw things up. A lot of the off-the-shelf NAT routers do a decent job of automatically configuring themselves, but there's no guarantees.<br>
