<br>
Moved into my roomates house. He had his pc all set up with a cable modem. I used my  4-port NAT router from d-link in-between the modem and his pc. put the driver disk in his pc and it configured the router from his set-up on his pc. Ran a 50' patch cable from one of the ports on the router to the uplink port on my hub and plugged in my 3 pc's. Not difficult at all. plus, he still can use 3 ports on the router if he ever wants to use his pc for anything other than solitaire <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=741435&amp;resize=true">My Gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dullfiinafv>DullfiinaFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cleric of Bristlebane</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/03 3:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2008.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mikkonen.org/dullfiina_eqpa.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Two PCs networked together.  I know there's a way</span><hr size=1> Speaking from the experience:<br>
<br>
No matter what connection you use, &quot;its all just networking&quot; so pretty much any configuration will do. But ok, you have Dialup so thats modem right ?<br>
<br>
So, what you have is modem, lets forget that part first. What you need *first* is to establish network between two of your machines, so both of them need a network card.<br>
<br>
So, you have both computers with network card now and you need a way to connect those two. Two ways, get a hub/switch and connect both machines to it OR get cross-over cable and connect the cards straight to each other.. The worst part here is to make the connection work between each other. <br>
<br>
When you have connection between the two machines work, its time to work on the internet connection. Ok, you have Dialup  so its pretty straight forward as you allready have it working.. Next thing to do is just configure internet connection sharing in your xp box (the one with the dialup connection too) and should be set to go.<br>
